ILESA – The Chairman, Ido Aiye­gunle Development Asso­ciation and Ogboni of Ido Aiyegunle, High Chief Toy­inbo Michael, has warned members of the public particularly land grabbers and land speculators not to buy nor sell from the land along Esa-Oke Road that terminated at Oke Obatala as violation of the warning would be visited with liti­gation. High Chief Toyinbo gave the warning during a chat with Daily Independent at Ilesa, Osun State last Monday. According to the Chair­man, Ido Aiyegunle Devel­opment Association since the demise of Oba Adekan­mi Ajayi Aseleese 1 some years ago, the association became the supervising au­thority on the land pending the installation of a new monarch for Ido Aiyegunle. Again, Ovrode Community Shuts Down Ughelli/Asaba Expressway For… Mr. Eno Is My Golden Boy, Wife Blows Hot He stated further that anytime any part of the land would be put for sale either for Industrial, Com­mercial and Residential purposes members of the public would be notified through radio and news­paper advertisements. The association warned that corporate organisa­tions and other groups of people who contravene the warning do so at their own risk. Ido Aiyegunle Commu­nity Association, however, explained that the warning became imperative as the community do not want to engage with any member of the public with force or litigation now. The association, how­ever, maintained that the community does not be­lieve in force to achieve success but peace stressing that it was why the early warning on the land.